
[1]perpetuate

   PERPET'UATE, v.t. [L. perpetuo.] To make perpetual; to eternize.

   1. To cause to endure or to be continued indefinitely; to preserve from
   extinction or oblivion; as, to perpetuate the remembrance of a great
   event or of an illustrious character. The monument in London
   perpetuates the remembrance of the conflagration in 1666. Medals may
   perpetuate the glories of a prince.

   2. To continue by repetition without limitation.
